<subsection xml:id="subsec-zero-indices" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Zero indices</title>
       
                <activity>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Work in Groups</alert>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Instructions</alert>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Choose any <m>3</m> natural numbers from the list below:
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <m>2, 5, 7, 10, 25, 100</m>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    For each chosen number:
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <ol marker="i)">
                                        <li>
                                            <p>
                                                Write two equal powers of the number.e.g <m> 2^3 \div 2^3</m>
                                            </p>
                                        </li>
                                        <li>
                                            <p>
                                                Simplify the expression formed.
                                            </p>
                                        </li>
                                    </ol>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Look at the pattern below and complete the missing values:
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    
                                    <m>
                                        2^4 = 16
                                    </m>
                                    <me>
                                        
                                    </me>
                                    <m>2^3 = 8</m>
                                    <me>
                                        
                                    </me>
                                    <m>2^2 = 4</m>
                                    <me>
                                        
                                    </me>
                                    <m> 2^1 = 2</m>
                                    <me>
                                        
                                    </me>
                                    <m>2^0 = ?</m> 
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    What happens when the exponent reaches zero?
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    Discuss your work with your fellow learners.
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                </statement>
            </activity>
            <p>
                <alert>Key Takeaway</alert>
            </p>
            <p>
                For any natural number <m>a</m>, if it is raised to the power of zero, the result is always <m>1</m>. 
            </p>
            <p>
                This means that <m>a^0 = 1</m> for any <m>a \neq 0</m>.
            </p>
            <p>
                For example, <me>
                    
                </me>
                <md>
                    <mrow>\frac{4^2}{4^2} = \amp 4^2 \div 4^2</mrow>
                    <mrow> = \amp 4^{2-2}</mrow>
                    <mrow>= \amp 4^0</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            
            <example>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                      Simplify <m>7^2 \times 7^0</m>  
                    </p>
                </statement>
                <solution>
                    <p>
                      By definition, <m>7^0 = 1</m>.  
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Therefore, 
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <md>
                            <mrow> 7^2 \times 7^0 = \amp  7^2 \times 1</mrow>
                            <mrow> =\amp 7^2 </mrow>
                            <mrow>= \amp 7 \times 7 </mrow>
                            <mrow> = \amp 49</mrow>
                        </md>
                    </p>
                    
                </solution>
            </example>

    
